4 HR____ HONORING MS. PHYLLIS CHUNN AT THE ROSETTA JAMES
5 FOUNDATION'S 20TH ANNUAL "HONORING OUR ELDERS DAY" GALA.
6
7 WHEREAS, with great joy and special pleasure, we
8 honor Ms. Phyllis Chunn as the special guest at the Rosetta
9 James Foundation's 20th Annual "Honoring Our Elders Day"
10 Gala at the Jackson Center in Huntsville, Alabama, on
11 Saturday, March 14, 2026; and
12 WHEREAS, Ms. Chunn was educated during the era of
13 school integration, attending Huntsville schools William
14 Hooper Councill High School and Lee High School; these
15 experiences broadened her worldview and strengthened her
16 resolve; after further study at North Alabama Business
17 College, she served as assistant to Dr. John Cashin during
18 his historic gubernatorial campaign, an experience that
19 introduced her to public service during a transformative
20 era; she later built a distinguished career in technology
21 and worked for IBM, MCI WorldCom, and Hewlett-Packard, where
22 she retired as a Senior Project Manager; and
23 WHEREAS, Ms. Chunn's life has been shaped by faith,
24 fortitude, and the power of storytelling; as a child, she
25 wrote plays and staged puppet performances for neighborhood
26 children, foreshadowing a lifelong creative calling;
27 inspired by Scripture, her Christ-centered stories explore
28 hope, resilience, and moral insight; she continues to
Page 1

hope, resilience, and moral insight; she continues to
HR232 INTRODUCED
29 delight children through storytelling and imaginative
30 gatherings in her cartoon-themed garden; and
31 WHEREAS, her life reflects a deep belief in community
32 and the adage that the "village" shapes and sustains each
33 generation; Ms. Chunn has quietly invested in mentoring
34 young people and supporting educational initiatives; through
35 faith, imagination, and lived wisdom, she continues to
36 uplift young hearts and inspire purposeful living; and
37 WHEREAS, the mission of the Rosetta James Foundation
38 is to honor the wisdom, service, and dedication of our
39 cherished senior citizens; the "Honoring Our Elders Day"
40 Gala is a heartfelt tribute to community and civic
41 volunteers 70 years of age and above who have dedicated
42 their lives to uplifting others and fostering positive
43 change; these remarkable individuals exemplify the very
44 spirit of compassion, leadership, and service that inspires
45 us all; and
46 WHEREAS, this annual celebration not only shines a
47 spotlight on these distinguished elders but also serves as a
48 platform to invest in the next generation of agents for
49 change; through the generous support of its attendees and
50 donors, the Gala raises vital funds to provide scholarships
51 for deserving students who embody the principles of
52 volunteerism, academic excellence, and civic engagement;
53 these outstanding students will also be recognized during
54 the event, connecting their bright futures to the enduring
55 legacies of those who came before them; and
56 WHEREAS, this year's Gala will be held at noon on
Page 2

WHEREAS, this year's Gala will be held at noon on
HR232 INTRODUCED
57 Saturday, March 14, at the Jackson Center; the extraordinary
58 contributions of our elders will be honored while future
59 leaders will be empowered to continue building a legacy of
60 service and excellence; now therefore,
61 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE
62 LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, That Ms. Phyllis Chunn will be
63 highly honored on an unforgettable afternoon filled with
64 inspiration, celebration, and community, and we endeavor to
65 continue uplifting and investing in those who make a
66 difference, both today and tomorrow.
